1. start website dev mode
cd Desktop/
django-admin startproject wordcount-project
cd wordcount-project/
python3 manage.py runserver


2. git terminal instructions:
cd Desktop/
cd wordcount-project/
git init *starts a git session
git status *tells which files are not committed
git add -A *gets files ready to commit
git status
git commit -m "This is my first commit" *commits file

create github repo

git remote add origin https://github.com/ryan-bradley-cowan/wordcount-project.git
git push -u origin master
git config --global user.name "Ryan Bradley Cowan"
git config --global user.email ryan.bradley.cowan@gmail.com


3. create virtual environment (this should be activated before doing step 1 and 2)
pip3 install virtualenv
cd Desktop/
virtualenv myvenv
source myvenv/bin/activate *to navigate into virtual environment
pip install django

4. .gitignore file templates
https://www.toptal.com/developers/gitignore

5. apps (in terminal)
python manage.py startapp blog
python manage.py startapp jobs

6. model fields for django
https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/3.2/ref/models/fields/

7. migrations
first tell python we have a new app for db. go to settings.py INSTALLED_APPS and add app
pip install pillow *needed to work with images
pyhton manage.py migrate
python manage.py makemigrations *see migrations.0001_initial.py for db code
pyhton manage.py migrate

8. admin url superuser
python manage.py createsuperuser
then go to admin page localhost:8000/admin and log in with credentials